body_html: @harshsp31 been awhile since I did this, but should just need to go to head of master in tensorflow/models, then I probably did something silly like cd into the tensorflow submodule folder and pull, but you should probably do git submodule update --recursive --remote in the tensorflow/models folder to update any and all submodules.

body: @harshsp31 been awhile since I did this, but should just need to go to head of master in tensorflow/models, then I probably did something silly like `cd` into the tensorflow submodule folder and pull, but you should probably do `git submodule update --recursive --remote` in the tensorflow/models folder to update any and all submodules.
